      "note_no": "20",
      "note": "\"Tubba'\" was the title borne by a succession of powerful Himyar kings who ruled for centuries over the whole of South Arabia, and were finally overcome by the Abyssinians in the fourth century of the Christian era. They are mentioned elsewhere in the Qur'an (50:14) as having denied the truth of resurrection and God's judgment."
